If rays emanating from a point actually meet at another point after reflection and/or refraction, that point is called the image of the first point.", "fibs": ["FD"]}
{"text": "The image is real if the rays actually converge to the point; it is virtual if the rays do not actually meet but appear to diverge from the point when produced backwards.", "fibs": ["image"]}
{"text": "An image is thus a point-to-point correspondence with the object established through reflection and/or refraction.", "fibs": ["image"]}
