{"text": "Another familiar observation is that the bottom of a tank filled with water appears to be raised (Fig.", "fibs": ["observation"]}
{"text": "For viewing near the normal direction, it can be shown that the apparent depth (h1) is real depth (h2) divided by the refractive index of the medium (water).", "fibs": ["direction"]}
{"text": "The refraction of light through the atmosphere is responsible for many interesting phenomena.", "fibs": ["refraction"]}
{"text": "For example, the Sun is visible a little before the actual sunrise and until a little after the actual sunset due to refraction of light through the atmosphere (Fig.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "By actual sunrise we mean the actual crossing of the horizon by the sun.", "fibs": ["sunrise"]}
