{"text": "The figure is highly exaggerated to show the effect.", "fibs": ["figure"]}
{"text": "The refractive index of air with respect to vacuum is 1.00029.", "fibs": ["index"]}
{"text": "Due to this, the apparent shift in the direction of the Sun is by about half a degree and the corresponding time difference between actual sunset and apparent sunset is about 2 minutes (see Example 9.5).", "fibs": ["shift"]}
{"text": "The apparent flattening (oval shape) of the Sun at sunset and sunrise is also due to the same phenomenon.", "fibs": ["shape"]}
